      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOOR BUSTER (5) bolted in two back before jumping an odds-on pop here last time out and pulling up with a slight issue. Happy to excuse that effort as her run prior was very good and rates highly here. Expecting her to bounce back to winning ways. THE LIONS' GATE (3) is racing well, winning by 1.9L in an impressive effort from the back of the pack at this track and trip. That effort stacks right up in this field and the form has already been franked. Can repeat the dose. HIGH PRECISION (1) got back to winning ways last start when scoring by 2.5L on the quick turnaround last week. Up to this trip is a query, though Riordan's claim comes in hand and she knows the mare well. Can go back-to-back. DIEGO DYNAMITE (6) can find the front and take catching from a favourable barrier. PAT'S LAST BANG (9) will appreciate this easier race today and can improve.",
